modemu2k: modemu2k (Hayes-style AT-command modem emulator)
modemu2k:
modemu2k: modemu2k bridges a serial-style interface to a TCP or Telnet
modemu2k: endpoint. It ships as a C library (libmodemu2k) exposing the
modemu2k: modem state machine, plus a small CLI built on top that allocates
modemu2k: a PTY and either reads stdin/stdout directly, forks a comm program
modemu2k: (minicom, picocom) on the slave, or accepts an incoming TCP
modemu2k: connection as the TTY. IPv4 and IPv6 are supported.
